Every page has 2 properties:

    - animation
    - entryAnimation

For every routechange there is a function changing animation property with 'to' and 'from' attributes and custom animation for exit.

Every page loads with initial animation property = entryAnimation. Doesn't need 'to' and 'from'. Will change to different exitanimation on route change.

_load() laadt de doelpagina (met entryAnimation)

ALS doelpagina geladen is EN ALS oorsprongpagine exitanimation afgelopen is, moet doelpagina zijn entryAnimation inladen.

hoe doelpagina laten weten dat de exitanimation van oorsprongpagina gedaan is zodat hij zijn entryAnimation kan inladen?

change name animatino to exitanimation? Since thats is its only use.

The entryAnimation is limited to 1 / page, unless we want to load a different one in at callback, dependent on originpage